{
  "texts": [
    "Given the present focus on appropriate conceptualisations of manipulation, these questions are out of scope for this paper.",
    "Nonetheless, at least two broad questions that crop up at the design stage have a bearing on appropriate conceptualisations nonetheless.",
    "For one, it might be thought that the conceptualisation question could be settled by design.",
    "Specifically, there may be ways to address the conceptualisation question through different alignment approaches in AI, which ultimately bottom-out in a machine learning approach.",
    "27 Kenton et al. (2021) discuss as the option to include human preferences in the training of the generative AI system (Christiano, 2017)."
  ]
}